-- GM IPO to have four lead underwriters: source
-- 
-- Fri Aug 13, 2010 5:21pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/08/13/us-gm-ipo-underwriters-idUSTRE67C4MN20100813

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - General Motors Co GM.UL will have four lead underwriters on its IPO, according to a source familiar with the situation. 

 The lead underwriters will be Bank of America Corp ( BAC.N ), Citigroup Inc ( C.N ), JPMorgan Chase & Co ( JPM.N ) and Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ), the source said. JPMorgan and Morgan Stanley helped the automaker prepare the paperwork for the IPO. Separately, GM is considering offering 20 percent to 30 percent of the IPO stock flotation to retail investors. IPOs typically sell 20 percent of their stock to retail investors. (Reporting by  Clare Baldwin ; editing by  Bernard Orr )